librix — Relative Index Library

Index-based data structures for shared memory.
This library provides relative (index-pointing) implementations of classic BSD
data structures—SLIST, LIST, STAILQ, TAILQ, CIRCLEQ, Red-Black tree, and
high-performance cuckoo hash tables—so you can store them directly in shared
memory or mmapped files without embedding raw pointers.

Pointer-free storage: heads and nodes store unsigned indices only.

1-origin indices: valid range 1..UINT_MAX-1; 0 is RIX_NIL (end/sentinel).

Per-call base pointer: APIs take base (your element array) to convert index⇄pointer on the fly.

C11, single header, no deps: drop it in and go.

