RIX_RB (Red-Black Tree)

Declarations & codegen

RIX_RB_ENTRY(type)

RIX_RB_HEAD(name)

RIX_RB_HEAD_INITIALIZER(var)

RIX_RB_INIT(head)

RIX_RB_PROTOTYPE(name, type, field, cmp)

RIX_RB_GENERATE (name, type, field, cmp) → emits full RB implementation using indices

Operations

RIX_RB_INSERT(name, head, base, elm) → returns existing node on duplicate, else NULL

RIX_RB_REMOVE(name, head, base, elm) → returns removed elm

RIX_RB_FIND(name, head, base, key)

RIX_RB_NFIND(name, head, base, key) (lower bound)

RIX_RB_MIN(name, head, base), RIX_RB_MAX(name, head, base)

RIX_RB_NEXT(name, base, elm), RIX_RB_PREV(name, base, elm)

Iteration

RIX_RB_FOREACH(x, name, head, base)

RIX_RB_FOREACH_REVERSE(x, name, head, base)

Comparator

int cmp(const type *a, const type *b);  /* strict weak ordering */

RIX_HASH (Cuckoo Hash Table)

A high-performance, index-based cuckoo hash table in hashtbl/rix_hash.h.
Stores fingerprints and 1-origin node indices in bucket arrays; no raw pointers.
Suitable for shared memory and file-backed regions.

Key lengths supported: 64, 128, 256, 512 bits.

Runtime SIMD dispatch: Generic / AVX2 / AVX-512 selected at startup via cpuid.

Design

Bucket layout (128 bytes = 2 cache lines, 64-byte aligned):

  uint32_t hash[16]   /* fingerprints                    */
  uint32_t idx[16]    /* 1-origin node indices (0=empty) */

Two candidate buckets per key:

  fp     = hash.val32[0] ^ hash.val32[1]
  fp_bk  = fp & mask  (non-zero; used for XOR bucket selection)
  bk0    = hash.val32[0] & mask
  bk1    = (bk0 ^ fp_bk) & mask   /* guaranteed bk0 != bk1 */

Kickout uses the XOR symmetry: alt(bk) = (bk ^ fp_bk) & mask.

Getting Started

  #include "hashtbl/rix_hash.h"

  /* 1. Typedef the element struct (bare identifier required by macros) */
  typedef struct mynode mynode;
  struct mynode {
      uint8_t  key[16];   /* 128-bit key */
      uint32_t value;
  };

  /* 2. Declare head – use the SAME name for HEAD and GENERATE */
  RIX_HASH_HEAD(myht);

  /* 3. Provide a hash function */
  static union rix_hash_hash_u my_hash(const void *key) { ... }

  /* 4. Generate the full API */
  RIX_HASH_GENERATE(myht, mynode, key, 128, my_hash)

  /* 5. Initialise once at program startup */
  rix_hash_arch_init();

  /* 6. Allocate 64-byte-aligned bucket array and node array */
  struct rix_hash_bucket_s *buckets = aligned_alloc(64, NB_BK * sizeof(*buckets));
  memset(buckets, 0, NB_BK * sizeof(*buckets));   /* zero = all slots empty */
  mynode *nodes = calloc(N, sizeof(*nodes));       /* 1-origin: nodes[0] = index 1 */

  struct myht head;
  RIX_HASH_INIT(&head, NB_BK);                    /* NB_BK must be a power of 2 */

  /* Single-shot operations */
  mynode *dup = myht_insert(&head, buckets, nodes, &nodes[i]);
  /* NULL → inserted; non-NULL → duplicate node; elm itself → table full */

  mynode *hit = myht_find(&head, buckets, nodes, key_ptr);

  mynode *rem = myht_remove(&head, buckets, nodes, key_ptr);

  myht_walk(&head, buckets, nodes, cb, arg);

  /* Staged (pipelined) find – hide memory latency across N requests */
  struct rix_hash_find_ctx_s ctx[4];
  const void *keys[4] = { ... };
  mynode *results[4];

  myht_hash_key4(ctx, &head, buckets, keys);   /* hash + bucket prefetch */
  myht_scan_bk4 (ctx, &head, buckets);         /* fingerprint scan       */
  myht_cmp_key4 (ctx, nodes, results);         /* full key compare       */

Important Notes

(a) typedef required: RIX_HASH_GENERATE uses type as a bare C identifier.
    Always declare typedef struct foo foo; before using foo as the type argument.

(b) Name consistency: the tag given to RIX_HASH_HEAD(name) and the first
    argument of RIX_HASH_GENERATE(name,...) must be identical.

(c) rix_hash_arch_init() must be called once before any hash table operation.
    It detects CPU features (AVX-512F, AVX2) and sets the dispatch table.

(d) Bucket array alignment: use aligned_alloc(64, ...) or posix_memalign
    to guarantee 64-byte alignment for best SIMD performance.

(e) Bucket count (nb_buckets) must be a power of 2 and at least 2.

(f) insert return values:
      NULL       – success
      other ptr  – duplicate node (key already present)
      elm itself – table full (kickout depth exhausted)

RIX_HASH API

Declarations & codegen

RIX_HASH_HEAD(name)                           /* declares struct name { mask, nb } */
RIX_HASH_INIT(head, nb_buckets)               /* initialise head */
RIX_HASH_GENERATE(name, type, key_field, key_len, hash_fn)

hash_fn signature: union rix_hash_hash_u hash_fn(const void *key);
key_len: 64, 128, 256, or 512 (bits)

Single-shot ops

type *name_find  (head, buckets, base, key)
type *name_insert(head, buckets, base, elm)
type *name_remove(head, buckets, base, key)
int   name_walk  (head, buckets, base, cb, arg)   /* cb: int(*)(type*,void*) */

Staged find (pipeline stages – find の構成要素)

void  name_hash_key (ctx,    head, buckets, key)   /* x1 */
void  name_scan_bk  (ctx,    head, buckets)
type *name_cmp_key  (ctx,    base)

void  name_hash_key2(ctx[2], head, buckets, keys[2])  /* x2 bulk */
void  name_scan_bk2 (ctx[2], head, buckets)
void  name_cmp_key2 (ctx[2], base, results[2])

void  name_hash_key4(ctx[4], head, buckets, keys[4])  /* x4 bulk */
void  name_scan_bk4 (ctx[4], head, buckets)
void  name_cmp_key4 (ctx[4], base, results[4])

Arch dispatch

void rix_hash_arch_init(void)   /* call once at startup; selects Generic/AVX2/AVX-512 */

Build

Standard: C11 (also builds with -std=gnu11).

Suggested flags:

-O3 -std=gnu11 -mavx2 -Wall -Wextra -Werror -pedantic
# Optional during testing:
-fsanitize=address,undefined -fno-omit-frame-pointer


Force-inline helper (optional):

#if defined(_MSC_VER)
  #define RIX_FORCE_INLINE __forceinline
#elif defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
  #define RIX_FORCE_INLINE __attribute__((always_inline)) inline
#else
  #define RIX_FORCE_INLINE inline
#endif

Concurrency

No internal synchronization. For multi-process or multi-thread writers, place operations under your own locks (e.g., futex, pthread mutex, or process-shared primitives). Readers/writers without locks are out of scope (RCU/lock-free would need additional design).

Testing

The project includes unit tests and fuzz tests (for each container, the RB tree,
and the cuckoo hash table) covering:

empty/singleton/multi transitions,

all insert/remove variants,

safe iteration while removing elements,

RB invariants (root black, no red-red, equal black height),

hash table: duplicate detection, staged pipeline correctness, walk count,
fuzz (random insert/find/remove verified against a reference model).

Integrate your own allocator/free-list to model persistent shared-memory scenarios.

